captions.text: I don't really have anything funny to say because my heart's kind of broken. Like this should be the best thing ever.

What?! *Fork clanks against plate* Get the fuck out!

So this is what blood tastes like?
Do I have anything on my nose?
Um. Uh, just like a little on the left.
There you go. You're good. You're good. You're gonna want the rest of that.

comments.text:
I think that guy that liked the blood pudding so much might be a cannibal. 
I would not have wanted to sit that close to him. 
What about Irish stew? My mom, who is 100% Irish , use to make the most 
wonderful Irish stew. When I returned to Ireland, on a long drive, I went 
to a restaurant next to a set of lakes. (It was not Kerry and I forgot 
where it was). I ordered Irish stew at this beautiful setting and it was 
horrible. I kept saying it was horrible, nothing like my mom's stew, and my 
friend from Limerick kept laughing at me. Looks can be deceiving. You can 
go to a place, with a beautiful view, and get a view only, nothing else.. I 
guess I wound up paying only for the view. It reminds me of the Mayweather 
and Pacman fight, but in the fight, I got nothing for my pay , so I guess I 
cannot complain about the restaurant, in Mother Ireland, where I at least 
got a beautiful view....
